Content:
> Steam accepted blank recovery codes for password resets<p>Sample buggy code (that I just made up):<p>(user_token is user supplied token, token is the correct token)<p><pre><code>  for(i = 0; i < strlen(user_token); i++) {
    if(user_token[i] != token[i]) return false;
  }
  return true;
</code></pre>
If code is blank this will falsely return true. This is also subject to truncation attacks.<p>I&#x27;m trying to think of a bug where blank fails, but truncated versions do not.
